polisci 420a american politics seminar i stanford university polisci 420a american politics seminar i jonathan wand autumn 2009 description this graduate seminar reviews various approaches to the study of american politics those important today as well as those that have been important in the past the course is organized around a selection of key questions in political science and we will focus on evaluating the analytical usefulness and empirical support of existing theories and ideas none of the questions are unique to american politics and comparative cases are also considered syllabus consult the syllabus for detailed description of a course requirements b readings c schedule contact information please consult the syllabus for email addresses office locations etc or jonathan wand's homepage http wand stanford edu revised september 9 2009
